      </div>
      <h1 class='title'>Civil enforcement of traffic contraventions</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='grand-committee-report-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HL Deb 29 April 2004 vol 660 c178GC</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_178gc' title='Col. 178GC &mdash; HL Deb 29 April 2004 vol 660 c178GC' name='column_178gc' href='#column_178gc' rel='bookmark'>178GC</a>
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0660P0-03625'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0660P0_20040429_GCR_357' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        1 (1) The appropriate national authority may issue guidance to any local authority undertaking civil enforcement powers under Part 6 of this Act or the <a href="/acts/london-local-authorities-and-transport-for-london-act-2003">London Local Authorities and Transport for London Act 2003</a> (c. iii) about any matter relating to the exercise by it of any power to impose civil penalties for road traffic contraventions.
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0660P0-03626'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0660P0_20040429_GCR_358' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (2) In exercising their powers of civil enforcement of traffic contraventions a local authority shall have regard to guidance under this section."
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0660P0-03627'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0660P0_20040429_GCR_359' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        The noble Viscount said: The Government have introduced Amendment No. 124, which deals with the issues in Amendment No. 118. I have a considerable speech to make&#x2014;my rant on behalf of the British motorist and his great fight-back. However, bearing in mind the time, it is best that I leave my speech for when we deal with the government amendments.
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0660P0-03628'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0660P0_20040429_GCR_360' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        [<span class="italic">Amendment No. 118 not moved. </span>]
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0660P0-03629'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0660P0_20040429_GCR_361' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        [<span class="italic">Amendments Nos. I I8A and 118B not moved.</span>]
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0660P0-03630'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0660P0_20040429_GCR_362' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        Schedule 7 agreed to.
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0660P0-03631'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0660P0_20040429_GCR_363' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        Clause 71 agreed to.
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0660P0-03632'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0660P0_20040429_GCR_364' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        Schedule 8 agreed to.
      </p>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0660P0-03633'>
        <a name='S5LV0660P0_20040429_GCR_365'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-matthew-evans' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S5LV0660P0_20040429_GCR_365' title='Link to this speech by Mr Matthew Evans' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-matthew-evans" title="Mr Matthew Evans">Lord Evans of Temple Guiting</a></cite>
          <p class='first-para'>
            This may be a convenient moment for the Committee to adjourn until Tuesday 4 May at 3.30 p.m. I hope that everybody has a very nice weekend.
          </p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0660P0-03634'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0660P0_20040429_GCR_366' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        The Committee adjourned at nine minutes before seven o'clock.
      </p>
